 natural setting in a distinct way. From the forest-framing reception center to the light-filtering bamboo huts, the elevated Metasequoia Wood Cottages, and the sculptural Pinecone Cabins, each element offers a unique perspective on the surrounding landscape\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1438\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hotel-design-architecture-layout-200625-306-01.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hotel-design-architecture-layout-200625-306-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hotel-design-architecture-layout-200625-306-01-940x704.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hotel-design-architecture-layout-200625-306-01-800x599.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hotel-design-architecture-layout-200625-306-01-768x575.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hotel-design-architecture-layout-200625-306-01-1536x1150.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe hotel’s reception center stands where a dilapidated wooden structure once sat. Instead of starting from scratch, the architects retained its original volume, creating a new building that feels deeply rooted in the site’s memory.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eFacing south, a wide picture window frames the forest like a living mural, while a band of clerestory windows to the north draws soft light from the bamboo grove behind. As guests enter, they cross an invisible threshold, from the outside world into the quiet rhythms of the woodland. This central structure sets the tone: grounded, minimal, and in constant dialogue with its surroundings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/202