ight=\"1440\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-01.jpg\" alt=\"Elevated among tall trees, these stilted wooden cottages offer an immersive canopy stay. Timber interiors bring guests closer to forest light, air, and sound.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-01-940x705.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-01-800x600.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-01-768x576.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-01-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-02.jpg\" alt=\"Elevated among tall trees, these stilted wooden cottages offer an immersive canopy stay. Timber interiors bring guests closer to forest light, air, and sound.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-02-940x752.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-02-800x640.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-02-768x614.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-02-1536x1229.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-03.jpg\" alt=\"Elevated among tall trees, these stilted wooden cottages offer an immersive canopy stay. Timber interiors bring guests closer to forest light, air, and sound.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-03.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-03-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-03-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-03-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/wood-cottage-hotel-rooms-200625-315-03-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Pinecone Cabins take their name and form from nature. Designed as modular units that adapt to varying terrain, they’re elevated above the forest floor to protect tree roots and allow the landscape to breathe.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith roofs that taper upward like pinecones, the cabins echo the metasequoia grove’s tall, narrow silhouette. Their compact footprint and organic geometry lend them both a sculptural quality and a deep sense of belonging, architecture as an extension of the forest itself.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-01.jpg\" alt=\"Lightweight and modular, these cabins take cues from pinecones and tree forms. Elevated design preserves the forest floor, while angled rooflines echo the grove’s vertical rhythm.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-01-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-02.jpg\" alt=\"Lightweight and modular, these cabins take cues from pinecones and tree forms. Elevated design preserves the forest floor, while angled rooflines echo the grove’s vertical rhythm.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-02-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-02-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-02-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-02-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1707\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03.jpg\" alt=\"Lightweight and modular, these cabins take cues from pinecones and tree forms. Elevated design preserves the forest floor, while angled rooflines echo the grove’s vertical rhythm.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03.jpg 1707w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03-940x1410.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-design-architecture-200625-317-03-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1703\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-01.jpg\" alt=\"Lightweight and modular, these cabins take cues from pinecones and tree forms. Elevated design preserves the forest floor, while angled rooflines echo the grove’s vertical rhythm.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-01-940x834.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-01-800x710.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-01-768x681.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-01-1536x1362.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-02.jpg\" alt=\"Lightweight and modular, these cabins take cues from pinecones and tree forms. Elevated design preserves the forest floor, while angled rooflines echo the grove’s vertical rhythm.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-02-940x752.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-02-800x640.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-02-768x614.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pinecone-cabin-hotel-room-design-interior-design-200625-317-02-1536x1229.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eDongmingshan Senyu Hotel it invites you to slow down. Every decision, from the stilted foundations to the bamboo facades, reflects a commitment to minimal intervention and long-term sustainability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotographer: Chen Xi Studio | Architects: GLA Architects\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
